dministrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: 1976 births, British individuals, Males,     and 2 more    Puddlemere United supporters   Wizards             English     Polski   Русский               Timothy Blenkinsop              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                   Timothy Blenkinsop   Biographical information  Born c. 1976    Physical information  Species Human   Gender Male    Relationship information  Family members Barnabus Blenkinsop (possibly)   [Source]  Timothy Blenkinsop (born c. 1976) was a Quidditch fan who supported Puddlemere United.[1] He was twenty-three when he attended a match between Puddlemere United and the Holyhead Harpies on 30 September, 1999.[1] These two teams had long been rivals, and, anticipating the possibility of crowd violence, the Ministry of Magic confiscated wands at the gates.[2] However, many attendees turned over fake wands.[2] Thus, when Wilda Griffiths, a Chaser for Puddlemere United who transferred from the Harpies earlier that year, disappeared mid-match, a riot broke out, and people were able to use their real wands.[2] Timothy got caught in the crossfire, and was left with a tail because of it, presumably due to a spell that hit him.[1]  Etymology The name "Timothy" is from the Greek name Τιμοθεος (Timotheos) meaning "honouring God", derived from τιμαω (timao) "to honour" and θεος (theos) "god". As an English name, Timothy was not used until after the Protestant Reformation.  Appearances Daily Prophet Newsletters Notes and references   ↑ 1.0 1.1 1.2 "Wizards, Witches and Beings: B" on the Harry Potter Lexicon  ↑ 2.0 2.1 2.2 "Daily Prophet newsletters" on The Harry Potter Lexicon              Categories         Categories:   1976 births    British individuals    Males    Puddlemere United supporters    Wizards             Languages      Polski Русский      *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, 